First Lady Melania Trump spent time with children from the Girls and Boys Club of Greater Washington, FBR Clubhouse in Ward 8. They visited the White House Kitchen Garden, where they learned about the importance of the outdoors and healthy eating. The National Park Service taught them how to harvest and plant, and shared the history of the garden and the White House beehive. Melania Trump spoke with the children about their own gardens at home and their favorite vegetables. She emphasized the importance of healthy and positive environments for children's well-being and praised the Kitchen Garden as a place for children to learn about healthy living and the history of the White House. Melania Trump expressed her happiness to be able to celebrate healthy living with the children and looked forward to future events in the garden.